                <h1>Abstract vs Background: Understanding the Key Differences</h1>
                <p>When writing an academic paper, understanding the difference between abstract and background is crucial. An abstract provides a concise summary of the research, including objectives, methods, results, and conclusions. In contrast, the background sets the stage, offering context, detailing prior work, and outlining the significance of the study.</p>
